The company will soon be letting users know if they liked, reacted to, or commented on posts with harmful misinformation about the virus that was removed by moderators.
Social media is awash in bad takes about the outbreak and platforms have begun to combat that misinformation.
The social network and other platforms have already taken steps to curb the wave of dangerous misinformation that has spread along with the coronavirus.
